      <abstract>Plans to build a Congregational church in Littleton, Colorado, were begun in 1958.
        Faith Congregational Church was formally gathered in 1959. The name of the church changed in
        1967 to Littleton United Church of Christ. The name of the church changed later to Ridge
        Road United Church. The church likely closed in 1993. This collection contains
        administrative records for the Ridge Road United Church in Littleton, Colorado, as well as
        an extensive collection of scrapbooks. The administrative records contain, primarily, the
        minutes of church meeting, The scrapbooks document the history of the church, largely
        through collected bulletins, worship programs, clippings, and photographs.</abstract>
