    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>Plans to build a Congregational church along Ridge Road, Littleton, Colorado, were begun in
        1958. The name of the newly gathered church was decided in November 1959 by a vote in favor
        of Faith Congregational Church. The church's first minister was Rev. Gordon Blunt. The name
        of the church changed in 1967 to Littleton United Church of Christ when the church also
        decided to join with the United Church of Christ. The name of the church changed again in
        the 1980s to Ridge Road United Church. The church likely closed in 1993.</p>
    </bioghist>
